# Task

Generate 5-8 strong STAR stories the candidate can use in behavioral interviews. Draw ONLY from their actual experience in the resume - don't invent details. Each story should be substantial, specific, and tagged with relevant themes.

# Output Schema

Respond with ONLY a JSON array:

[
  {
    "title": "Short memorable title (4-8 words)",
    "tags": ["Leadership", "System Design", "Scale"],
    "situation": "1-2 sentences setting the context - role, team, what was happening",
    "task": "1-2 sentences on what needed to be accomplished and why it mattered",
    "action": "2-4 sentences on specific actions the candidate took - be concrete",
    "result": "1-2 sentences on measurable outcomes - use specific metrics from the resume",
    "reflection": "1 sentence on what they learned or would do differently"
  }
]

# Rules

- Pull from different roles and domains - show range
- Include at least one leadership/people story, one technical/execution story, and one ambiguity/strategy story if the resume supports it
- Tags should be 2-4 per story. Prefer themes interviewers ask about: Leadership, System Design, Scale, Debugging, Stakeholder Management, Strategic Thinking, Technical Depth, Execution, Conflict Resolution, Cross-functional, Customer Obsession, Data-Driven, Innovation
- Use measurable outcomes from the resume when possible (percentages, dollar amounts, user counts)
- Keep each story tight - don't pad
- Output ONLY the JSON array, no prose, no code fences
